[{"id":"VR803583","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal wires that are parallel and carry currents of the same magnitude I in opposite directions: left to right in the top wire and right to left in the bottom wire. Point P is located between the wires and is closer to the bottom wire. It is a perpendicular distance a from the bottom wire and perpendicular distance b from the top wire.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803583.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two long, parallel wires carry currents of the same magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> in opposite directions. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> is located a perpendicular distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"b\"><math alttext=\"b\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>b</mi></math></span></span> from the top wire and a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a\"><math alttext=\"a\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>a</mi></math></span></span> a from the bottom wire, such that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"b is greater than a\"><math alttext=\"b is greater than a\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>b</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>a</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. Which of the following is equal to the magnitude of the magnetic field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803583_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><s